700037f-a.title: Bronx: 134th Street (East) - Brown Place
700037f-a.text:
East 134th Street, east from but not including Brown Place, showing
buildings, on the north side of the street, being razed to make way for
the construction of an approach to the Triborough Bridge.
May 11, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

700031f-b.title: Bronx: 134th Street (East) - Brown Place
700031f-b.text:

April 12, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The sahme, at a later date, after the houses were raed to make way

May 11, 1937.

700675f-a.title: Bronx: Brown Place - 134th Street (East)
700675f-a.text:
140 to 150 Brown Place, east side, north from East 134th to 135th
Streets, showing a 2, a 4 and a 5-story buildings in the process of
demolition.
May 11, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
